text: Nosal (lit. 'The Nose') is a mountain in the Tatra Mountains of Poland, and is 1,206 metres AMSL at its highest. It is a popular tourist destination located near the Polish town of Zakopane, particularly for skiing and gliding. ==References== ==External links== Category:Mountains of Poland Category:Mountains of the Western Carpathians Category:Western Tatras
title: Nosal
